00:44:03,270 --> 00:44:05,110
Scott: Oh, I thought there were two cathedrals in that one city.

732
00:44:05,771 --> 00:44:06,869
Rym: No, no, I don't think there were.

733
00:44:07,290 --> 00:44:07,336
Scott: Oh.

734
00:44:07,873 --> 00:44:08,350
Rym: I don't remember.

735
00:44:08,792 --> 00:44:08,948
Rym: Alright.

736
00:44:09,150 --> 00:44:32,210
Scott: Anyway, real quick, king-making, it doesn't work in many games, but it works in- And you have the ability to help other players and hurt other players, and everyone knows what everyone's score is.

737
00:44:32,390 --> 00:44:37,990
Rym: You pick one other dude, or maybe two other dudes in the game, and you decide they are not going to win.

738
00:44:38,210 --> 00:44:39,520
Rym: I know they're not going to win.

739
00:44:39,661 --> 00:44:40,710
Rym: They're not smart enough to win.

740
00:44:41,190 --> 00:44:47,970
Rym: So what I'm going to do is team up with them, and I'll do things that benefit me and them, and they'll do things that benefit them and me.

741
00:44:48,651 --> 00:44:52,190
Rym: And we'll push ourselves up at the expense of everyone else in the game.

742
00:44:52,392 --> 00:44:54,270
Scott: The people who have a chance of competing with you.

743
00:44:54,470 --> 00:44:58,270
Rym: So now, it's really just a game between me and the people I made kings with.

744
00:44:58,550 --> 00:45:00,950
Rym: So we're the kings, and everyone else, it doesn't matter.

745
00:45:01,430 --> 00:45:03,010
Rym: And then I screw them at the critical moment.

746
00:45:03,512 --> 00:45:06,010
Rym: Or I just know that they won't be able to capitalize on that.

747
00:45:06,470 --> 00:45:07,756
Scott: So let's give an example.

748
00:45:07,836 --> 00:45:10,930
Scott: It's a game between me, Rym, Joe, and John.

749
00:45:12,071 --> 00:45:16,230
Scott: We know that Joe and John are probably going to kick my ass.

750
00:45:16,470 --> 00:45:17,669
Scott: Rym, he sucks, he can't win.

751
00:45:18,451 --> 00:45:23,710
Scott: So what I do is I get a whole bunch of victory points by teaming up with Rym.

752
00:45:24,210 --> 00:45:27,050
Scott: Because Joe and John are the only people who can possibly beat me at this game.

753
00:45:27,430 --> 00:45:32,770
Rym: Yeah, like anytime one of us has a big city, he'll jump onto it, or help it finish, that sort of thing.

754
00:45:33,550 --> 00:45:35,870
Scott: So me and Rym now have like 100 points each.

755
00:45:36,470 --> 00:45:39,870
Scott: And Joe and John basically can't win this game because they're so far behind.

756
00:45:40,070 --> 00:45:43,350
Scott: We teamed up and gave each other points, and it was great.

757
00:45:43,971 --> 00:45:45,469
Scott: Now I fuck Rym in the ass and I win.

758
00:45:46,471 --> 00:45:49,090
Scott: Because Joe and John can't possibly win, they're way down there.

759
00:45:49,391 --> 00:45:50,589
Scott: So all they have to do is fuck Rym.

760
00:45:52,211 --> 00:45:58,550
Rym: This doesn't work too well in a lot of games, because if you're playing with people who are all good, it still works, but it doesn't work in the same way.

761
00:45:58,870 --> 00:46:04,050
Scott: Because if Rym was good, I'd be like, alright, Joe and John are better than Rym, but Rym's still good.

762
00:46:04,470 --> 00:46:06,990
Scott: I'll team up with Rym, and oh, he fucked me first, dammit.

763
00:46:07,150 --> 00:46:13,810
Rym: And if it's four people who are all equal in skill, it's still a valid strategy, but at this point, all you're doing is increasing the odds of victory.

764
00:46:14,192 --> 00:46:16,866
Rym: Because now you have a 50% chance of winning instead of a 25% chance.

765
00:46:18,050 --> 00:46:19,910
Rym: Because two people are now eliminated from the game.

